params.operator: The address of the operator whose ejection is being cancelled.
params.recipient: The address to which the gas refund will be sent.
params.sigma: The BLS signature of the operator.

completeEjection(address,bytes).details: Any ejector can complete an ejection process, but the deposit is returned to the ejector who initiated it.

params.cooldown: The number of seconds that must pass before a new ejection can be initiated after a previous one.

params.delay: The number of seconds that must pass after initiation before an ejection can be completed.              This is also the time guaranteed to a challenger to cancel the ejection.

params.operator: The address of the operator to eject.
params.quorums: The quorums associated with the ejection process.

addEjectorBalance(uint256).notice: Adds to an escrow for the ejector to use in ejection processes.

cancelEjection().notice: Cancels the ejection process for the message sender. Refunds gas to the caller.

cancelEjectionByEjector(address).notice: Cancels the ejection process initiated by a ejector.

cancelEjectionWithSig(address,(uint256[2.notice: Cancels the ejection process for a given operator with their signature. Refunds the deposit to the recipient.

completeEjection(address,bytes).notice: Completes the ejection process for an operator. Transfers the deposit back to the ejector.

ejectionCooldown().notice: Returns the cooldown for ejection initiations per operator.

ejectionDelay().notice: Returns the delay for ejection processes.

ejectionQuorums(address).notice: Returns the quorums associated with the ejection process for a given operator.

ejectionTime(address).notice: Returns whether an ejection process has been initiated for a given operator.

getDepositToken().notice: Returns the address of the token used for ejection deposits and refunds.

getEjector(address).notice: Returns the address of the ejector for a given operator. If the returned address is zero, then there is no ejection in progress.

getEjectorBalance(address).notice: Returns the current book-kept balance for an existing ejector.

lastEjectionInitiated(address).notice: Returns the timestamp of the last ejection proceeding initiated for a given operator.

semver().notice: Returns the semantic version of the contract implementation. Refer to https://semver.org/

setCooldown(uint64).notice: Sets the cooldown for ejection processes.

setDelay(uint64).notice: Sets the delay for ejection processes.

startEjection(address,bytes).notice: Starts the ejection process for an operator. Takes a deposit from the ejector.

withdrawEjectorBalance(uint256).notice: Withdraws from the ejector's escrow balance that is not currently in use for an ejection process.
